ParameterItem.Doc: Verification mode determines whether or not monitors and drivers are on. Possible values are ON or Off.
ParameterItem.Name: VERIF_MODE

ParameterItem.Doc: Synthesis mode determines whether or not special synthesis constructs are used. Possible values are ON or Off.
ParameterItem.Name: SYNTH_MODE

ParameterItem.Doc: Width of the Fraction for the multiplier (default is IEEE Double, 52 bit)
ParameterItem.Name: FractionWidth

ParameterItem.Doc: Width of the exponent for the multiplier (default is IEEE Double, 11 bit)
ParameterItem.Name: ExponentWidth

ParameterItem.Doc: Which architecture is tested? Cascaded multiply accumulate or Fused? (Pick:Cascade/Fused)
ParameterItem.Name: Architecture

ParameterItem.Doc: Enable denormals parameters to enable handling denormal values of inputs A and B correctly (YES/NO)
ParameterItem.Name: EnableDenormals

ParameterItem.Doc: Tree radix
ParameterItem.Name: Radix

ParameterItem.Doc: Booth type. (1 for no booth, 2 is default, 3 and 4 may sometimes be useful when Width is very large)
ParameterItem.Name: BoothType

ParameterItem.Doc: Summation tree type. (Supported trees: Wallace, Array, ZM) (Soon:OS1Tree, OS2Tree)
ParameterItem.Name: TreeType

ParameterItem.Doc: Hints for layout positioning (Supported layouts: Square, Parallelogram)
ParameterItem.Name: LayoutShape

ParameterItem.Doc: Number of test transactions to run (can be overriden at runtime using the '+NumTrans=value' command line notation)
ParameterItem.Name: NumTrans

ParameterItem.Doc: Seed for random values(can AND SHOULD be overriden at runtime using the '+Seed=value' command line notation)
ParameterItem.Name: Seed

Allowed values for NamedTransCtrl are capital letters 'A' through 'Z' or it can be left empty
